**🟡 SUGGESTION — `useUserProfile` returns a new object reference on every render**

`readStorage()` is called directly in the hook body, returning a new parsed object each render. This means:
1. `profile` is never referentially stable
2. Any `useCallback`/`useMemo` depending on `profile` will always recompute
3. `triggerDownload` in WeekAtAGlanceStrip has `profile` in its deps — it's recreated every render

This doesn't cause bugs since `handleDownload` guards with `isDownloading`, but it defeats the purpose of `useCallback`. Consider storing the parsed profile in `useState`:

```ts
export function useUserProfile() {
  const [profile, setProfile] = useState<UserProfile | null>(readStorage);

  const saveProfile = useCallback((name: string, githubUsername: string) => {
    const p = { name: name.trim(), githubUsername: normalizeGithubUsername(githubUsername) };
    writeStorage(p);
    setProfile(p);
  }, []);

  return { profile, saveProfile };
}
```

This gives referential stability to `profile` until the next `saveProfile` call.

